#X text 1070 4 # YOU CAN USE NOISE SEPARATION \, TAKING INCOMING SIGNAL AND SEPARATE IT INTO BINS. BUT THEN ON BIN TO BIN BASIS \, DECIDE IF WHAT WE HAVE IS SINUSOIDAL OR NON SINUSOIDAL. THEN WE GENERATE TWO OUTPUT. ONE FOR THE STUFF THAT LOOKED SINUSOIDAL AND THE OTHER ONE FOR THE STUFF THAT DO NOT LOOK SINUSOIDAL. THEN YOU TIME STRETCH THE SINUSOIDAL STUFF WITH A PHASE-VOCODER ALGORITHM WHICH WORKS FINE FOR IT AND THE NON-SINUSOIDAL STUFF WITH A GRANULATOR STRETCHING ALOGIRITHM WHICH WORKS GREAT FOR IT BUT BAD FOR PITCHY STUFF. THEN MIX THE TWO., f 38;
